West Virginia has been hit harder than any other state by the Fentanyl crisis and I support taking all available steps to stop the flow of illegal opioids into our country.

@POTUS and his administration are committed to making our country safe.

Any attempt by Democrats to overturn the National Emergency is putting this nation at risk.

Important news for WV!

@POTUS’ Major Disaster Declaration has been amended to include public assistance for Boone and Raleigh Counties as well as individual assistance for Raleigh County.

Visit the link to learn more. https://t.co/Naka9DIafW

Big news for WV!

@EPA has taken an important step towards granting West Virginia the authority we need to properly implement Class VI wells for carbon capture. This is essential to protecting our ability to provide reliable, baseload power in West Virginia through coal and natural gas, while reducing our power and manufacturing sector emissions.
https://t.co/Rh98VMLM4u

What a fantastic night!

This election, the American people sent a clear message: The American people are unhappy with the direction this country was going in and it’s time to turn things around under President Trump.

@SenateGOP is ready and excited to get to work in the majority to make life better for all Americans.

The latest attempt by the Biden-Harris administration to forgive massive amounts of student loan debt is just another example of their scheme to transfer debt to hardworking American taxpayers. @usedgov estimates that this rule will cost taxpayers $112 billion over ten years. 

This is completely unfair and irresponsible.
@SenateGOP continues to work towards solutions for hardworking American students and families instead of recklessly forgiving student loans.

Biden-Harris inflation is costing West Virginia families on average $891 MORE per month. 

This is unsustainable.

@SenateGOP is fighting to make everyday life affordable again. https://t.co/0C2eYqDlkC

Over the last 4 years, the Biden-Harris administration has demonstrated weak leadership on the world stage.

We must get back to “peace through strength” and get serious about our national security and supporting our allies.

@SenateGOP is ready to do just that.
